      "content": "Taking ibuprofen with food can help reduce stomach irritation, so try to take it with a meal or snack that's high in fat, like a sandwich or some nuts. This can help slow down the absorption of the medication and minimize stomach upset. Additionally, you can also consider taking a stomach-soothing supplement, like Tums or Rolaids, to help neutralize stomach acid. Just be sure to follow the recommended dosage and consult with your doctor if you have any concerns.",
